article_text:
We interrupt the presidential campaign to review developments in Washington, where Congress may or may not try to pass a budget. Perhaps Republicans might even decide to set an example for the candidates about how politics works when practiced competently.

For weeks the House GOP has been conducting another internal debate about the best fiscal strategy. Congress is supposed to pass the annual budget resolution by April 15 that sets spending targets for 2017. But backbenchers and outside groups continue to rebel against...
